00:21:09,940 --> 00:21:14,606
I think you should rest and come back next week.

272
00:21:14,606 --> 00:21:15,889
I can't rest.

273
00:21:15,890 --> 00:21:19,019
I have to show and promote a music contest next week.

274
00:21:19,019 --> 00:21:21,670
I'll have no time for friends.

275
00:21:24,600 --> 00:21:26,886
What is happening here?

276
00:21:27,560 --> 00:21:32,086
We're discussing the show Sarawat has to perform.

277
00:21:32,086 --> 00:21:33,999
I can perform. Just let me.

278
00:21:33,999 --> 00:21:36,179
I asked your doctor.

279
00:21:36,179 --> 00:21:40,633
Besides the injured knee, you have an injured wrist too.

280
00:21:40,633 --> 00:21:42,213
I can't let you perform in this condition.

281
00:21:42,214 --> 00:21:44,070
My wrist is okay now.

282
00:21:44,070 --> 00:21:46,780
My knee won't be a problem. Let me perform.

283
00:21:46,780 --> 00:21:48,513
No.

284
00:21:51,300 --> 00:21:54,489
We don't want any substitution.

285
00:21:54,490 --> 00:21:57,900
Without you, it's not Control S.

286
00:22:01,180 --> 00:22:02,913
Please.

287
00:22:03,460 --> 00:22:05,293
Let me perform.

288
00:22:09,860 --> 00:22:14,259
P'Dim, will my show be good enough to substitute Control S?

289
00:22:15,040 --> 00:22:17,340
What's got into your head?

290
00:22:21,390 --> 00:22:24,690
I am not as good as Sarawat.

291
00:22:24,690 --> 00:22:28,100
But I can perform by myself.

292
00:22:28,100 --> 00:22:32,119
Great! I will perform a guitar solo after Tine's show.

293
00:22:34,660 --> 00:22:36,806
Me too.

294
00:22:39,530 --> 00:22:42,293
Us too.

295
00:22:42,293 --> 00:22:43,669
It doesn't sound so bad.

296
00:22:43,669 --> 00:22:46,600
We give this stage to newbies.

297
00:22:46,600 --> 00:22:51,760
It might motivate more people to step up and join the contest.

298
00:22:58,660 --> 00:23:00,810
Do you all know that?

299
00:23:01,400 --> 00:23:07,546
When you are on stage, you carry the club's reputation with you.

300
00:23:10,520 --> 00:23:12,060
I do.

301
00:23:12,060 --> 00:23:16,286
This club accepted me and taught me guitar lessons.

302
00:23:16,286 --> 00:23:20,953
It's time for me to repay it.

303
00:23:37,110 --> 00:23:40,506
P'Dim is crazy enough to let Tine perform.

304
00:23:43,100 --> 00:23:46,499
Fong, talk to him. He only listens to you.

305
00:23:46,499 --> 00:23:47,959
Try to change his mind.

306
00:23:47,960 --> 00:23:50,959
What's wrong with him playing for the club?

307
00:23:50,960 --> 00:23:54,339
He is a newbie. He doesn't have enough time to practice.

308
00:23:54,339 --> 00:23:57,320
The first time on stage is tough.

309
00:23:58,000 --> 00:23:59,739
I don't want him to fail.

310
00:23:59,740 --> 00:24:03,019
Do you know why Tine hasn't said yes to your confession?

311
00:24:03,020 --> 00:24:04,209
How does that have to do with anything here?

312
00:24:04,210 --> 00:24:11,726
Tine was always the one taking care of his ex.

313
00:24:11,726 --> 00:24:17,399
But now he is the one being taken care of. I guess he is not used to it.

314
00:24:17,399 --> 00:24:24,386
He might want to prove that he is good enough to be with you.

315
00:24:27,090 --> 00:24:29,446
Don't be happy just yet.

316
00:24:29,446 --> 00:24:33,860
If he fails this time, he might get too discouraged.

317
00:24:33,860 --> 00:24:36,923
He might withdraw himself from a relationship with you forever.

318
00:24:44,890 --> 00:24:46,623
Thanks.

319
00:24:56,560 --> 00:25:00,712
Your food is right here. I'm going to go practice now.

320
00:25:00,712 --> 00:25:06,059
Hey! I hurt my knee, not my eyes.

321
00:25:06,059 --> 00:25:09,259
You can practice here. I can be your mentor.

322
00:25:11,040 --> 00:25:12,773
Fine.

323
00:25:17,790 --> 00:25:20,340
I will get you a chair.

324
00:25:24,180 --> 00:25:26,213
Thank.

325
00:25:52,906 --> 00:25:55,406
What are you looking at?

326
00:25:55,406 --> 00:26:00,160
I'm just thinking… Ever since you gave me this guitar,

327
00:26:00,160 --> 00:26:03,259
I haven't named it yet.

328
00:26:03,259 --> 00:26:06,059
Is it the right time to name a guitar? Practice.

329
00:26:06,059 --> 00:26:07,729
I am serious here.

330
00:26:07,730 --> 00:26:13,273
If you were a guitar, you would want to play for the owner who gave you a nice name.

331
00:26:14,960 --> 00:26:17,230
Up to you then.

332
00:26:17,230 --> 00:26:23,100
Well... What kind of name do you like then?

333
00:26:23,100 --> 00:26:26,800
Something that describes me.

334
00:26:28,740 --> 00:26:30,473
Ringworm.

335
00:26:31,600 --> 00:26:33,900
Just call yourself that.

336
00:26:37,630 --> 00:26:38,940
Scrubb?

337
00:26:38,940 --> 00:26:40,760
- Scrubb?
- Yes.

338
00:26:40,760 --> 00:26:42,410
Don't you feel pity for them at all?

339
00:26:42,410 --> 00:26:46,240
Don't ruin their band by naming your guitar that.

340
00:26:47,330 --> 00:26:49,089
What name do you want then?

341
00:26:49,090 --> 00:26:52,846
Just pick one already, Nuisance.

342
00:26:52,846 --> 00:26:54,799
Stop being picky and practice.

343
00:26:54,800 --> 00:26:56,500
Nuisance!

344
00:26:56,500 --> 00:26:59,925
That's right. Nuisance!

345
00:26:59,925 --> 00:27:02,160
Freaking right for my guitar.

346
00:27:04,200 --> 00:27:07,299
You are awesome! You are clever.

347
00:27:07,299 --> 00:27:10,640
Let me see your music chords.

348
00:27:18,630 --> 00:27:21,230
Are you playing a Scrubb song?

349
00:27:21,230 --> 00:27:24,006
Yes. Why?

350
00:27:24,006 --> 00:27:26,160
The first time having a girlfriend,

351
00:27:26,160 --> 00:27:28,230
the first heartbreak,

352
00:27:28,230 --> 00:27:30,070
the first music video recording.

353
00:27:30,070 --> 00:27:31,940
Scrubb songs took part in all of them.

354
00:27:31,940 --> 00:27:34,113
This will be my first time on stage.

355
00:27:34,113 --> 00:27:37,163
How can I play a song from other bands?

356
00:27:37,163 --> 00:27:38,686
You're right.

357
00:27:39,790 --> 00:27:44,659
I am jealous of Scrubb. They are your first of many things.

358
00:27:44,659 --> 00:27:46,830
I want to be Scrubb.

359
00:27:47,660 --> 00:27:49,260
Why?

360
00:27:49,260 --> 00:27:52,020
So that I can be with you both, when you're happy and sad.

361
00:27:53,060 --> 00:27:55,173
I want to be Scrubb.

362
00:27:57,020 --> 00:27:58,853
Cheesy!

363
00:28:01,260 --> 00:28:03,390
Let me practice already.

364
00:28:03,390 --> 00:28:07,506
Otherwise, the true sadness will come if I can't play.

365
00:28:15,730 --> 00:28:19,349
Wrong. Press harder.

366
00:28:19,349 --> 00:28:21,283
Wrong.

367
00:28:21,283 --> 00:28:23,999
Wrong. Press more firmly.

368
00:28:23,999 --> 00:28:25,260
Isn't this firm enough?

369
00:28:25,260 --> 00:28:28,489
If it's firmly enough, it won't sound wrong. Press harder.

370
00:28:29,426 --> 00:28:31,640
Wrong. Press harder.

371
00:28:32,460 --> 00:28:36,600
Here. Press harder.

372
00:28:36,600 --> 00:28:38,070
Now play.

373
00:28:39,113 --> 00:28:41,953
This is called right.

374
00:28:41,953 --> 00:28:43,913
Memorize it.

375
00:28:44,780 --> 00:28:47,699
Try it. Give me a pick.

376
00:28:47,699 --> 00:28:49,860
Nobody holds a pick as you do.

377
00:28:49,860 --> 00:28:55,649
Look. Use your point finger like this.

378
00:28:55,649 --> 00:28:58,290
Spare the edge.

379
00:28:58,290 --> 00:29:01,480
Grab it together with your thumb and you strum it.

380
00:29:02,329 --> 00:29:04,040
Give me your hand.

381
00:29:04,990 --> 00:29:07,186
Here.

382
00:29:07,186 --> 00:29:10,780
Put a pick on your point finger.

383
00:29:10,780 --> 00:29:14,326
Leave the edge.

384
00:29:14,326 --> 00:29:17,940
Press it with your thumb.

385
00:29:20,970 --> 00:29:25,003
Tine, will you marry me?

386
00:29:26,640 --> 00:29:28,480
What the hell?

387
00:29:28,480 --> 00:29:31,930
You're teaching me to hold a pick, not putting on a wedding ring.

388
00:29:33,040 --> 00:29:35,726
Okay. Keep going!

389
00:29:41,030 --> 00:29:43,230
Why are you smiling?

390
00:29:43,230 --> 00:29:45,153
Who is?

391
00:30:01,360 --> 00:30:03,360
Does it hurt your fingers?

392
00:30:04,220 --> 00:30:07,339
Stop. Let me see.

393
00:30:23,610 --> 00:30:24,966
All of them hurt?

394
00:30:24,966 --> 00:30:27,220
Yes.

395
00:30:27,220 --> 00:30:29,340
Just take a break.

396
00:30:29,340 --> 00:30:33,012
If you practice too hard and hurt your fingers, you can't perform anyway.

397
00:30:33,013 --> 00:30:34,700
Let me have a look.

398
00:30:35,460 --> 00:30:38,620
See? Your fingers are about to bleed.

399
00:30:38,620 --> 00:30:41,470
You have to be able to play when the day comes.

400
00:30:47,190 --> 00:30:50,453
I'm trying to be gentle, but this is hard.

401
00:30:51,830 --> 00:30:53,663
Sorry.

402
00:31:01,000 --> 00:31:02,660
You know what.

403
00:31:03,246 --> 00:31:07,660
No one has ever put a band-aid on for me before in my life.

404
00:31:09,520 --> 00:31:12,100
And do you think I have done this for anyone?

405
00:31:26,820 --> 00:31:28,793
Marry me?

406
00:31:31,280 --> 00:31:33,973
Again? Stop it!

407
00:31:35,520 --> 00:31:37,253
It's done.

408
00:31:38,030 --> 00:31:40,106
Thank you.

409
00:31:42,190 --> 00:31:46,560
Take a break for a while until your fingers heal.

410
00:31:46,560 --> 00:31:50,520
Listen to the song in the meantime.

411
00:31:57,940 --> 00:32:00,000
I said no practice.

412
00:32:00,000 --> 00:32:01,833
Put it down.

413
00:32:45,930 --> 00:32:48,530
[To help you see the chords more clearly.]

414
00:33:53,640 --> 00:33:57,052
Good timing. We are teaming up.

415
00:33:57,052 --> 00:33:59,660
This game, I will play your opponent.

416
00:33:59,660 --> 00:34:01,140
What?

417
00:34:01,140 --> 00:34:03,940
Be my guess. Play for the team you want.

418
00:34:20,880 --> 00:34:23,480
What the heck is your problem?

419
00:34:23,480 --> 00:34:25,900
That was one hell of a tackle.

420
00:34:35,560 --> 00:34:37,180
Ouch! Shit!

421
00:34:39,190 --> 00:34:41,380
What are you playing?

422
00:34:41,380 --> 00:34:43,760
I'm doing what you did to my brother.

423
00:34:43,760 --> 00:34:46,380
Yes! I am Sarawat's brother!

424
00:34:46,380 --> 00:34:48,150
Fuck you!

425
00:34:59,320 --> 00:35:01,892
You have an appointment for the x-ray tomorrow.

426
00:35:01,893 --> 00:35:05,253
I am not available tomorrow morning.

427
00:35:06,320 --> 00:35:09,109
Can we postpone it for later?

428
00:35:09,109 --> 00:35:11,199
Your doctor is free only tomorrow morning.

429
00:35:11,200 --> 00:35:13,446
After that, he is fully booked.

430
00:35:13,446 --> 00:35:15,573
We can't postpone it.

431
00:35:17,880 --> 00:35:19,413
Wat.

432
00:35:20,990 --> 00:35:22,623
Wat.

433
00:35:24,160 --> 00:35:25,881
- Wat!
- Yes.

434
00:35:25,881 --> 00:35:27,731
What is on your mind?

435
00:35:28,430 --> 00:35:30,320
Nothing.

436
00:35:30,320 --> 00:35:35,150
The nurse told me you have to come for an x-ray tomorrow.

437
00:35:35,150 --> 00:35:38,280
Just come. I will be fine.

438
00:35:38,280 --> 00:35:40,126
But you are performing.

439
00:35:40,126 --> 00:35:44,853
Do you think I went through all the practice just to bother you at the end?

440
00:35:49,980 --> 00:35:52,520
Can you take me somewhere today?

441
00:35:53,350 --> 00:35:55,083
Where?

442
00:36:08,320 --> 00:36:11,060
Why do you want to come here?

443
00:36:11,060 --> 00:36:15,940
I can't come to see you tomorrow.

444
00:36:15,940 --> 00:36:19,473
Just take it as a big rehearsal.

445
00:36:21,040 --> 00:36:23,140
- Play?
- Yes. Go up on stage.

446
00:36:23,140 --> 00:36:24,940
I'll be your audience.

447
00:36:27,530 --> 00:36:30,350
Come on. If you can't perform for one person,

448
00:36:30,350 --> 00:36:33,290
you can't perform in front of a bunch of people tomorrow.

449
00:36:51,990 --> 00:36:54,480
Why are you fidgeting?

450
00:36:57,300 --> 00:36:58,860
I don't know.

451
00:36:58,860 --> 00:37:03,626
Being up here makes me nervous.

452
00:37:10,640 --> 00:37:12,850
Hey! What are you doing?

453
00:37:12,850 --> 00:37:14,040
Filming you.

454
00:37:14,040 --> 00:37:18,540
Imagine yourself as a protagonist in a movie.

455
00:37:18,540 --> 00:37:21,459
You are a well-trained guitar player.

456
00:37:21,460 --> 00:37:25,779
It's a scene where you're about to perform in front of many people.

457
00:37:25,779 --> 00:37:27,646
They are screaming and cheering for you.

458
00:37:27,646 --> 00:37:30,192
You are so great. It's the ending scene of the movie.

459
00:37:30,192 --> 00:37:31,624
A happy ending, you know?

460
00:37:31,625 --> 00:37:33,960
- The ending scene?
- Yes. A happy ending.

461
00:37:33,960 --> 00:37:36,680
That makes me even more nervous.

462
00:37:36,680 --> 00:37:41,100
Well. It's not a big movie. It's just a short film.

463
00:37:41,100 --> 00:37:43,500
Only a small project for your class.

464
00:37:43,500 --> 00:37:46,890
A short film for class? It still makes me nervous.

465
00:37:46,890 --> 00:37:48,090
I can't.

466
00:37:48,090 --> 00:37:51,020
Let's say it's just a video clip, not a film.

467
00:37:51,020 --> 00:37:55,160
A video clip that only I can see.

468
00:37:55,160 --> 00:37:56,540
- Only you?
- Yes.

469
00:37:56,540 --> 00:37:58,840
- You sure?
- Yes.

470
00:37:58,840 --> 00:38:01,000
Fine then.

471
00:38:01,000 --> 00:38:04,730
3, 2, 1. Action!

472
00:38:04,730 --> 00:38:08,050
What? Action?

473
00:38:08,050 --> 00:38:10,340
I mean… You can play now.

474
00:38:10,340 --> 00:38:12,512
You can start now. Start.

475
00:38:12,512 --> 00:38:13,573
- Now?
- Yes.

476
00:38:13,573 --> 00:38:15,130
Should I play now?

477
00:38:15,130 --> 00:38:16,240
Action!

478
00:38:16,240 --> 00:38:19,400
- Now?
- Yes. Action!

479
00:38:37,440 --> 00:38:41,550
Tine! Are you okay?

480
00:38:42,980 --> 00:38:45,461
- Sarawat!
- What are you guys doing here?

481
00:38:45,461 --> 00:38:47,540
We're bringing snacks for Sarawat.

482
00:38:47,540 --> 00:38:50,040
- He is not here.
- Is he still in recovery?

483
00:38:50,040 --> 00:38:55,460
Yes. But… if you leave them here,

484
00:38:55,460 --> 00:38:58,960
I promise Sarawat will get them. Each one of them.

485
00:38:58,960 --> 00:39:00,399
It's okay.

486
00:39:00,399 --> 00:39:01,990
Leave them here.

487
00:39:11,000 --> 00:39:14,890
Are you ready, Tine? The event will commence soon.

488
00:39:14,890 --> 00:39:16,423
I am.

489
00:39:17,760 --> 00:39:20,300
Just leave for now.

490
00:39:20,300 --> 00:39:23,280
- Come back again when I'm done greeting. Okay?
- Yes.

491
00:39:23,280 --> 00:39:27,580
Tine, keep fighting. We are rooting for you here.

492
00:39:30,200 --> 00:39:32,153
Come back later.

493
00:39:39,730 --> 00:39:44,049
Welcome everyone to our Music Club shows.

494
00:39:44,050 --> 00:39:48,119
Our club members will perform acoustic songs for you.

495
00:39:48,119 --> 00:39:52,340
If you're ready, let's welcome the first show on stage.

496
00:39:56,270 --> 00:39:58,166
Go and slay.

497
00:40:14,010 --> 00:40:19,040
Hi, guys. My name is Tine…

498
00:40:21,270 --> 00:40:24,930
Tine, Mr. Chic! Let's cheer for him!

499
00:40:28,230 --> 00:40:31,930
Hi, guys! I am Tine, Mr. Chic. The one and only.

500
00:40:31,930 --> 00:40:34,170
I'm going to play you a song.

501
00:40:34,170 --> 00:40:37,970
Some of you might not know this song. But I have practiced very hard for this.

502
00:40:37,970 --> 00:40:40,233
Give him a big hand!

